  "title": "do our best to inform the user on some missing index configuration",
  "body": "Let's say I add any widget that need to have a particular attribute configured as a facet, I would want the code after the first result is received to tell me \"Error: you must add ... as an attribute for faceting\" if I did not do it.\n\nWhat do you think?\n\nWhat are the others guesses we can make?\n\nOriginal idea by @seafoox \n\nWarn when:\n- asking for any widget that requires some attribute to be an attributeForFaceting and the attribute is not\n- asking for a numeric refinement and the attribute values are not numeric\n- using a toggle with something than is not a boolean attribute where we expect one\n",
